{
    "audio_file": "data/processed\\Bad Habit_cleaned.wav",
    "language": "en",
    "segments": [
        {
            "start": 0.0,
            "end": 16.76,
            "text": " When I was first learning to meditate, the instruction was to simply pay attention to"
        },
        {
            "start": 16.76,
            "end": 20.84,
            "text": " my breath and when my mind wandered to bring it back."
        },
        {
            "start": 20.84,
            "end": 27.36,
            "text": " Sounded simple enough, yet I'd sit on these silent retreats, sweating through t-shirts"
        },
        {
            "start": 27.36,
            "end": 29.240000000000002,
            "text": " in the middle of winter."
        },
        {
            "start": 29.28,
            "end": 32.64,
            "text": " I'd take naps every chance I got because it was really hard work."
        },
        {
            "start": 32.64,
            "end": 35.440000000000005,
            "text": " Actually, it was exhausting."
        },
        {
            "start": 35.440000000000005,
            "end": 40.32,
            "text": " The instruction was simple enough, but I was missing something really important."
        },
        {
            "start": 40.32,
            "end": 43.120000000000005,
            "text": " So why is it so hard to pay attention?"
        },
        {
            "start": 43.120000000000005,
            "end": 47.44,
            "text": " Well, studies show that even when we're really trying to pay attention to something,"
        },
        {
            "start": 47.44,
            "end": 52.96,
            "text": " like maybe this talk, at some point about half of us will drift off into a daydream"
        },
        {
            "start": 52.96,
            "end": 56.36,
            "text": " or have this urge to check our Twitter feed."
        },
        {
            "start": 56.36,
            "end": 59.040000000000006,
            "text": " So what's going on here?"
        },
        {
            "start": 59.04,
            "end": 62.879999999999995,
            "text": " It turns out that we're fighting one of the most evolutionarily conserved learning"
        },
        {
            "start": 62.879999999999995,
            "end": 67.28,
            "text": " processes currently known in science, one that's conserved back to the most basic"
        },
        {
            "start": 67.28,
            "end": 69.88,
            "text": " nervous systems known to man."
        },
        {
            "start": 69.88,
            "end": 73.36,
            "text": " This reward-based learning process is called positive and negative reinforcement"
        },
        {
            "start": 73.36,
            "end": 76.2,
            "text": " and basically goes like this."
        },
        {
            "start": 76.2,
            "end": 77.88,
            "text": " We see some food that looks good."
        },
        {
            "start": 77.88,
            "end": 80.6,
            "text": " Our brain says, calories, survival."
        },
        {
            "start": 80.6,
            "end": 83.28,
            "text": " We eat the food, we taste it, taste good."
        },
        {
            "start": 83.28,
            "end": 87.03999999999999,
            "text": " And especially with sugar, our body sends a signal to our brain that says,"
        },
        {
            "start": 87.04,
            "end": 91.32000000000001,
            "text": " remember what you're eating and where you found it."
        },
        {
            "start": 91.32000000000001,
            "end": 96.52000000000001,
            "text": " We lay down this context-dependent memory and learn to repeat the process next time."
        },
        {
            "start": 96.52000000000001,
            "end": 101.0,
            "text": " See food, eat food, feel good, repeat."
        },
        {
            "start": 101.0,
            "end": 103.60000000000001,
            "text": " Trigger behavior reward."
        },
        {
            "start": 103.60000000000001,
            "end": 105.96000000000001,
            "text": " Simple, right?"
        },
        {
            "start": 105.96000000000001,
            "end": 109.36000000000001,
            "text": " Well, after a while, our creative brain say, you know what?"
        },
        {
            "start": 109.36000000000001,
            "end": 112.96000000000001,
            "text": " You can use this for more than just remembering where food is."
        },
        {
            "start": 112.96000000000001,
            "end": 116.72,
            "text": " You know, next time you feel bad, why don't you try eating something"
        },
        {
            "start": 116.72,
            "end": 119.76,
            "text": " good so you'll feel better?"
        },
        {
            "start": 119.76,
            "end": 121.72,
            "text": " We thank our brains for the great idea."
        },
        {
            "start": 121.72,
            "end": 125.8,
            "text": " Try this and quickly learn that if we eat chocolate or ice cream,"
        },
        {
            "start": 125.8,
            "end": 128.72,
            "text": " when we're mad or sad, we feel better."
        },
        {
            "start": 128.72,
            "end": 131.84,
            "text": " Same process, just a different trigger."
        },
        {
            "start": 131.84,
            "end": 134.92,
            "text": " Instead of this hunger signal coming from our stomach,"
        },
        {
            "start": 134.92,
            "end": 139.12,
            "text": " this emotional feeling sad triggers others to eat."
        },
        {
            "start": 139.12,
            "end": 143.64,
            "text": " Maybe in our teenage years, we were inert at school"
        },
        {
            "start": 143.68,
            "end": 146.24,
            "text": " and we see those rebel kids outside smoking and think,"
        },
        {
            "start": 146.24,
            "end": 149.88000000000002,
            "text": " hey, I want to be cool, so we start smoking."
        },
        {
            "start": 149.88000000000002,
            "end": 153.60000000000002,
            "text": " The Marlboro man wasn't a dork and that was no accident."
        },
        {
            "start": 153.60000000000002,
            "end": 158.0,
            "text": " See cool, smoke to be cool, feel good, repeat."
        },
        {
            "start": 158.0,
            "end": 160.76000000000002,
            "text": " Trigger behavior reward."
        },
        {
            "start": 160.76000000000002,
            "end": 164.0,
            "text": " And each time we do this, we learn to repeat the process"
        },
        {
            "start": 164.0,
            "end": 165.96,
            "text": " and it becomes a habit."
        },
        {
            "start": 165.96,
            "end": 170.92000000000002,
            "text": " So later, feeling stressed out triggers that urge to smoke a cigarette"
        },
        {
            "start": 170.92000000000002,
            "end": 173.32000000000002,
            "text": " or to eat something sweet."
        },
        {
            "start": 173.32,
            "end": 176.16,
            "text": " Now with these same brain processes,"
        },
        {
            "start": 176.16,
            "end": 178.07999999999998,
            "text": " we've gone from learning to survive"
        },
        {
            "start": 178.07999999999998,
            "end": 181.0,
            "text": " to literally killing ourselves with these habits,"
        },
        {
            "start": 181.0,
            "end": 184.28,
            "text": " obesity and smoking among the leading preventable causes"
        },
        {
            "start": 184.28,
            "end": 186.32,
            "text": " of morbidity and brutality of the world."
        },
        {
            "start": 187.48,
            "end": 188.72,
            "text": " So back to my breath."
        },
        {
            "start": 189.79999999999998,
            "end": 192.2,
            "text": " What if instead of fighting our brains"
        },
        {
            "start": 192.2,
            "end": 194.72,
            "text": " or trying to force ourselves to pay attention,"
        },
        {
            "start": 194.72,
            "end": 196.95999999999998,
            "text": " we instead tapped into this natural reward-based"
        },
        {
            "start": 196.95999999999998,
            "end": 200.6,
            "text": " learning process but added a twist?"
        },
        {
            "start": 200.6,
            "end": 202.35999999999999,
            "text": " What if instead we just got really curious"
        },
        {
            "start": 202.36,
            "end": 204.84,
            "text": " about what was happening in a momentary experience?"
        },
        {
            "start": 204.84,
            "end": 206.72000000000003,
            "text": " I'll give you an example."
        },
        {
            "start": 206.72000000000003,
            "end": 208.72000000000003,
            "text": " In my lab, we studied whether mindfulness training"
        },
        {
            "start": 208.72000000000003,
            "end": 210.24,
            "text": " could help people quit smoking."
        },
        {
            "start": 211.24,
            "end": 214.04000000000002,
            "text": " Now, just like trying to force myself to pay attention"
        },
        {
            "start": 214.04000000000002,
            "end": 216.88000000000002,
            "text": " on my breath, they could try to force themselves"
        },
        {
            "start": 216.88000000000002,
            "end": 219.24,
            "text": " to quit smoking and the majority of them"
        },
        {
            "start": 219.24,
            "end": 222.84,
            "text": " had tried this before and failed on average six times."
        },
        {
            "start": 224.0,
            "end": 225.04000000000002,
            "text": " Now with mindfulness training,"
        },
        {
            "start": 225.04000000000002,
            "end": 226.68,
            "text": " we dropped a bit about forcing"
        },
        {
            "start": 226.68,
            "end": 229.68,
            "text": " and instead focused on being curious."
        },
        {
            "start": 229.68,
            "end": 232.88,
            "text": " In fact, we even told them to smoke."
        },
        {
            "start": 232.88,
            "end": 234.8,
            "text": " What? Yeah, we said, go ahead and smoke."
        },
        {
            "start": 234.8,
            "end": 238.44,
            "text": " Just be really curious about what it's like when you do."
        },
        {
            "start": 238.44,
            "end": 240.20000000000002,
            "text": " And what did they notice?"
        },
        {
            "start": 240.20000000000002,
            "end": 242.84,
            "text": " Oh, here's an example from one of our smokers."
        },
        {
            "start": 242.84,
            "end": 244.64000000000001,
            "text": " She said, mindful smoking,"
        },
        {
            "start": 244.64000000000001,
            "end": 248.0,
            "text": " smells like stinky cheese and tastes like chemicals."
        },
        {
            "start": 248.0,
            "end": 248.84,
            "text": " Yuck!"
        },
        {
            "start": 249.76000000000002,
            "end": 253.20000000000002,
            "text": " Now, she knew cognitively that smoking was bad for her."
        },
        {
            "start": 253.20000000000002,
            "end": 255.76000000000002,
            "text": " That's why she joined our program."
        },
        {
            "start": 255.76000000000002,
            "end": 258.76,
            "text": " What she discovered just by being curiously aware"
        },
        {
            "start": 258.76,
            "end": 263.32,
            "text": " when she smoked was that smoking tastes like shit."
        },
        {
            "start": 266.4,
            "end": 270.44,
            "text": " Now, she moved from knowledge to wisdom."
        },
        {
            "start": 270.44,
            "end": 272.08,
            "text": " She moved from knowing in her head"
        },
        {
            "start": 272.08,
            "end": 276.08,
            "text": " that smoking was bad for her to knowing it in her bones."
        },
        {
            "start": 276.08,
            "end": 278.36,
            "text": " And the spell of smoking was broken."
        },
        {
            "start": 278.36,
            "end": 281.59999999999997,
            "text": " She started to become disenchanted with her behavior."
        },
        {
            "start": 283.08,
            "end": 285.15999999999997,
            "text": " Now, the prefrontal cortex,"
        },
        {
            "start": 285.15999999999997,
            "end": 286.64,
            "text": " that youngest part of our brain"
        },
        {
            "start": 286.64,
            "end": 288.71999999999997,
            "text": " from an evolutionary perspective,"
        },
        {
            "start": 288.72,
            "end": 291.48,
            "text": " it understands on an intellectual level"
        },
        {
            "start": 291.48,
            "end": 292.8,
            "text": " that we shouldn't smoke."
        },
        {
            "start": 292.8,
            "end": 296.6,
            "text": " And it tries its hardest to help us change our behavior,"
        },
        {
            "start": 296.6,
            "end": 297.96000000000004,
            "text": " to help us stop smoking,"
        },
        {
            "start": 297.96000000000004,
            "end": 299.84000000000003,
            "text": " to help us stop eating that second,"
        },
        {
            "start": 299.84000000000003,
            "end": 302.06,
            "text": " that third, that fourth cookie."
        },
        {
            "start": 303.04,
            "end": 304.44000000000005,
            "text": " We call this cognitive control."
        },
        {
            "start": 304.44000000000005,
            "end": 308.04,
            "text": " We're using cognition to control our behavior."
        },
        {
            "start": 308.04,
            "end": 310.28000000000003,
            "text": " Unfortunately, this is also the first part"
        },
        {
            "start": 310.28000000000003,
            "end": 312.84000000000003,
            "text": " of a brain that goes offline when we get stressed out,"
        },
        {
            "start": 312.84000000000003,
            "end": 314.56,
            "text": " which isn't that helpful."
        },
        {
            "start": 314.56,
            "end": 317.04,
            "text": " Now, we can all relate to this in our own experience."
        },
        {
            "start": 317.04,
            "end": 319.76000000000005,
            "text": " We're much more likely to do things like yell at our spouse"
        },
        {
            "start": 319.76000000000005,
            "end": 321.56,
            "text": " or kids when we're stressed out or tired,"
        },
        {
            "start": 321.56,
            "end": 323.92,
            "text": " even though we know it's not going to be helpful."
        },
        {
            "start": 323.92,
            "end": 325.6,
            "text": " We just can't help ourselves."
        },
        {
            "start": 327.24,
            "end": 329.44,
            "text": " Now, when the prefrontal cortex goes offline,"
        },
        {
            "start": 329.44,
            "end": 331.64000000000004,
            "text": " we fall back into our old habits,"
        },
        {
            "start": 331.64000000000004,
            "end": 334.48,
            "text": " which is why this disenchantment is so important."
        },
        {
            "start": 334.48,
            "end": 335.96000000000004,
            "text": " Seeing what we get from our habits"
        },
        {
            "start": 335.96000000000004,
            "end": 338.40000000000003,
            "text": " helps us understand them in an even level,"
        },
        {
            "start": 338.40000000000003,
            "end": 339.52000000000004,
            "text": " to know we're in our bones."
        },
        {
            "start": 339.52000000000004,
            "end": 340.96000000000004,
            "text": " So we don't have to force ourselves"
        },
        {
            "start": 340.96000000000004,
            "end": 343.12,
            "text": " to hold back or restrain ourselves from behavior."
        },
        {
            "start": 343.12,
            "end": 346.52000000000004,
            "text": " We're just less interested in doing it in the first place."
        },
        {
            "start": 346.52,
            "end": 349.03999999999996,
            "text": " And this is what mindfulness is all about."
        },
        {
            "start": 349.03999999999996,
            "end": 350.96,
            "text": " Seeing really clearly what we get"
        },
        {
            "start": 350.96,
            "end": 353.64,
            "text": " when we get caught up in our behaviors,"
        },
        {
            "start": 353.64,
            "end": 357.24,
            "text": " becoming disenchanted on a visceral level,"
        },
        {
            "start": 357.24,
            "end": 360.15999999999997,
            "text": " and from this disenchanted stance, naturally letting go."
        },
        {
            "start": 361.03999999999996,
            "end": 364.47999999999996,
            "text": " This isn't to say that, oof, magically we quit smoking,"
        },
        {
            "start": 364.47999999999996,
            "end": 366.2,
            "text": " but over time, as we learn to see more"
        },
        {
            "start": 366.2,
            "end": 368.44,
            "text": " and more clearly the results of our actions,"
        },
        {
            "start": 368.44,
            "end": 370.88,
            "text": " we let go of old habits and form new ones."
        },
        {
            "start": 372.24,
            "end": 374.4,
            "text": " The paradox here is that mindfulness"
        },
        {
            "start": 374.4,
            "end": 376.4,
            "text": " is just about being really interested"
        },
        {
            "start": 376.40000000000003,
            "end": 377.72,
            "text": " in getting close and personal"
        },
        {
            "start": 377.72,
            "end": 379.00000000000006,
            "text": " with what's actually happening"
        },
        {
            "start": 379.00000000000006,
            "end": 382.04,
            "text": " in our body's and minds from moment to moment."
        },
        {
            "start": 382.04,
            "end": 384.36,
            "text": " This willingness to turn toward our experience"
        },
        {
            "start": 384.36,
            "end": 386.24,
            "text": " rather than trying to make unpleasant cravings"
        },
        {
            "start": 386.24,
            "end": 387.88000000000005,
            "text": " go away as quickly as possible."
        },
        {
            "start": 388.88000000000005,
            "end": 391.44000000000005,
            "text": " And this willingness to turn toward our experience"
        },
        {
            "start": 391.44000000000005,
            "end": 395.04,
            "text": " is supported by curiosity, which is naturally rewarding."
        },
        {
            "start": 395.04,
            "end": 396.84000000000003,
            "text": " What does curiosity feel like?"
        },
        {
            "start": 396.84000000000003,
            "end": 397.68000000000006,
            "text": " It feels great."
        },
        {
            "start": 399.08000000000004,
            "end": 401.44000000000005,
            "text": " And what happens when we get curious?"
        },
        {
            "start": 401.44000000000005,
            "end": 402.92,
            "text": " We start to notice that cravings"
        },
        {
            "start": 402.92,
            "end": 404.88000000000005,
            "text": " are simply made up of body sensations."
        },
        {
            "start": 404.88,
            "end": 407.15999999999997,
            "text": " Oh, there's tightness, there's tension,"
        },
        {
            "start": 407.15999999999997,
            "end": 408.84,
            "text": " there's restlessness,"
        },
        {
            "start": 408.84,
            "end": 411.04,
            "text": " and that these body sensations come and go."
        },
        {
            "start": 411.96,
            "end": 414.96,
            "text": " These are bite-sized pieces of experiences"
        },
        {
            "start": 414.96,
            "end": 417.0,
            "text": " that we can manage from moment to moment"
        },
        {
            "start": 417.0,
            "end": 418.44,
            "text": " rather than getting clobbered"
        },
        {
            "start": 418.44,
            "end": 422.6,
            "text": " by this huge, scary craving that we choke on."
        },
        {
            "start": 422.6,
            "end": 425.08,
            "text": " In other words, when we get curious,"
        },
        {
            "start": 425.08,
            "end": 427.96,
            "text": " we step out of our old fear-based"
        },
        {
            "start": 427.96,
            "end": 432.08,
            "text": " reactive habit patterns and we step into being."
        },
        {
            "start": 432.08,
            "end": 434.96,
            "text": " We become this inner scientist"
        },
        {
            "start": 434.96,
            "end": 438.24,
            "text": " where we're eagerly awaiting that next data point."
        },
        {
            "start": 438.24,
            "end": 442.76,
            "text": " Now, this might sound too simplistic to affect behavior,"
        },
        {
            "start": 442.76,
            "end": 444.84,
            "text": " but in one study we found that mindfulness training"
        },
        {
            "start": 444.84,
            "end": 447.03999999999996,
            "text": " was twice as good as gold standard therapy"
        },
        {
            "start": 447.03999999999996,
            "end": 449.24,
            "text": " at helping people quit smoking."
        },
        {
            "start": 449.24,
            "end": 450.59999999999997,
            "text": " So it actually works."
        },
        {
            "start": 451.88,
            "end": 454.68,
            "text": " And when we studied the brains of experienced meditators,"
        },
        {
            "start": 454.68,
            "end": 457.03999999999996,
            "text": " we found that parts of a neural network"
        },
        {
            "start": 457.03999999999996,
            "end": 458.56,
            "text": " of self-referential processing"
        },
        {
            "start": 458.56,
            "end": 461.28,
            "text": " called the default mode network were at play."
        },
        {
            "start": 461.28000000000003,
            "end": 464.36,
            "text": " Now, one current hypothesis is that a region of this network"
        },
        {
            "start": 464.36,
            "end": 466.6,
            "text": " called the posterior cerebral cortex"
        },
        {
            "start": 466.6,
            "end": 469.32000000000005,
            "text": " is activated not necessarily by craving itself,"
        },
        {
            "start": 469.32000000000005,
            "end": 471.72,
            "text": " but when we get caught up in it and get sucked in"
        },
        {
            "start": 471.72,
            "end": 473.68,
            "text": " and it takes us for a ride."
        },
        {
            "start": 473.68,
            "end": 477.20000000000005,
            "text": " In contrast, when we let go, step out of the process"
        },
        {
            "start": 477.20000000000005,
            "end": 479.76000000000005,
            "text": " just by being curiously aware of what's happening,"
        },
        {
            "start": 479.76000000000005,
            "end": 481.64000000000004,
            "text": " the same brain region quiets down."
        },
        {
            "start": 483.44000000000005,
            "end": 484.84000000000003,
            "text": " Now we're testing app"
        },
        {
            "start": 484.84000000000003,
            "end": 487.48,
            "text": " and online-based mindfulness training programs"
        },
        {
            "start": 487.48,
            "end": 490.68,
            "text": " that target these four mechanisms"
        },
        {
            "start": 490.68,
            "end": 493.12,
            "text": " and ironically, just the same technology"
        },
        {
            "start": 493.12,
            "end": 495.16,
            "text": " that's driving us to distraction"
        },
        {
            "start": 495.16,
            "end": 497.8,
            "text": " to help us step out of our unhealthy habit patterns"
        },
        {
            "start": 497.8,
            "end": 501.8,
            "text": " of smoking, of stress-eating, and other addictive behaviors."
        },
        {
            "start": 501.8,
            "end": 504.2,
            "text": " Now, remember that bit about context-dependent memory?"
        },
        {
            "start": 504.2,
            "end": 507.24,
            "text": " We can deliver these tools to people's fingertips"
        },
        {
            "start": 507.24,
            "end": 509.56,
            "text": " in the context that matter most."
        },
        {
            "start": 509.56,
